caption: Very historic church. A great place for adoration. They have there very long adoration times in the week. It's near the train station Paris est. So you can spent there your time. Before or after traveling. It has a warm atmosphere and the people there are very welcoming. Priest are there which is seldom.
A very nice religious edifice close to Gare du Nord. It played a great role in Parisian history

while walking along the canal Saint Martin we decided to follow a major street to locate a very beautiful church we had heard about.. we strolled over to 68 Boulevard de Magenta to observe this beautiful historic church in the Gothic Style.. it is a very rewarding walk... as noted in a brochure there are concerts available to attend...
Loved this place! Not the prettiest but the spirt of love was so alive here! I walked away heartened that a church could make others feel better and make a difference in their neighborhood.

As a Catholic, I can confirm that is a Roman Catholic Church. I received the Eucharist here and the Sunday mass was exactly the same as the one in my missal (although obviously in French). After the 11am mass (which I think was about an hour) they had exposition.
A very nice and small place to visit. Beautifully kept

St Vincent de Paul spent 20 Years here as a Parish Priest during his time he collaborated well with Louise de Marillac who was the mother superior for the Daughters of  Charity
Nice and quiet church. Need some renovation. Classified historical monument. You feel so close to the idea of eternity when you take a seat in here.

As I sat in this cathedral, something came over me. A sense of joy and love swept through my mind and a presence whispered in my ear to "let it effect you." So I did. I can't explain it, but a lot of emotional pain went away that day. I'm spiritual but not religious and I saw a lot of art in Paris that weekend that impacted me in far different ways then ever before. But this was different.

Old church from medivial times. Catholic architecture is another point of attraction. Very good peaceful ambience, just in contrast to the outside noisy and busy vicinity of East Paris railway station.

15th Century church on one of the main routes down from and back to the Gare de L'Est and Gare de Nord. So a good place to stop,  reflect and pray for the multitude around you. Lots of side chapels,  but don't miss the one behind the main altar.  Essential down time after a trip to this sometimes frenetic city.

Beautiful church with fun park for children next to it. Prayer-filled mass last evening. Glory to God.
